President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Vaughn F. Bishop as the Deputy Director of the Central Intelligence Agency. Bishop has a long and successful career with the Central Intelligence Agency, joining in 1981. He has held various analyst and senior management positions, including serving as the National Intelligence Officer for Africa and Vice-Chair of the National Intelligence Council. Bishop retired from the CIA in 2011 but was later asked to return as the CIA ombudsman for analytic objectivity during the agency's modernization effort. He holds a bachelor's, master's, and doctorate degree from Northwestern University.